<p><b>David Clayton-Thomas</b> (born <b>David Henry Thomsett</b>; 13 September 1941) is an <a href="England" title="England">English</a>-born <a href="Canada" title="Canada">Canadian</a> <a href="Musician" title="Musician">musician</a> and <a href="Singer" title="Singer" class="mw-redirect">singer</a> best known as the lead vocalist for the <a href="United_States" title="United States">American</a> band <a href="Blood,_Sweat_&_Tears" title="Blood, Sweat &amp; Tears">Blood, Sweat &amp; Tears</a>. Clayton-Thomas has maintained a busy solo career over the years as well.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
<tr>
<td>
